commit message:
First commit for SDCardTrac-er, adding basic files from Eclipse
workspace.

Fixes to FileObserverService to hook to correct directories.
Android manifest includes service name.

Updates to ensure all directories are watched correctly.
Need fixes to rename paths of moved directories.

Added periodic event list update/clear logic.
All control paths hooked up correctly.
Service intimation while alarm wakes from deep-sleep TBD.

Added SQLite backend functions.
File modification recording working (with duplicate entry filtering).

Brought up GUI with basic configuration functions.
Persistence across Activity life-cycle still not handled well.

Added GraphView (com.jjoe64.graphview.GraphView).
Library and Activity added, functionality not up yet.
Updated service for finer stop control.
Graph activity now plots basic tracking graph.
Added Spinner selector for update interval.

Added more functionality to graph, customised GraphView for showing
sample selected.

Enhanced graph for multi-line labels on X axis and some basic sanity
check of graph data.
Added refresh menu to graph, refactoring GraphView changes in progress
Manifest updated to trigger service when media is mounted.

Start alarms and service on bootup if watching is enabled.
Refactored Alarm related code into AlarmHelper class.
Create dummy entry on startup and reformat log message

Refined event logging

Instead of manually iterating through event list to filter redundancy, use a HashMap
Unified GraphView with top level gradle file
